                                                                            nicebnf:hasTextContent """Management

Allergy with classical symptoms of vomiting, colic and diarrhoea caused by specific foods such as cow's milk or shellfish should be managed by strict avoidance. The condition should be distinguished from symptoms of occasional food intolerance in those with irritable bowel syndrome. Sodium cromoglicate may be helpful as an adjunct to dietary avoidance.

