        <p outputclass=\"title\">Inhaler devices for children under 5 years with chronic asthma (August 2000)</p>
        <p>A child’s needs and likelihood of good compliance should govern the choice of inhaler and spacer device; only then should cost be considered.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>corticosteroid and bronchodilator therapy should be delivered by pressurised metered-dose inhaler and spacer device, with a facemask if necessary;</li>
